<td>University of KwaZulu-Natal (MA) Graduate School, City University of New York (Master of Philosophy), graduate School, City University of New York (Doctor of Philosophy)</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Adam Habib</b> is a citizen of <a href="/wiki/South_Africa" title="South Africa">South Africa</a>, a professor of <a href="/wiki/Political_science" title="Political science">political science</a>, and the current <a href="/wiki/Chancellor_(education)" title="Chancellor (education)">Vice-Chancellor</a> and <a href="/wiki/Principal_(university)" title="Principal (university)" class="mw-redirect">Principal</a> of the <a href="/wiki/University_of_the_Witwatersrand" title="University of the Witwatersrand">University of the Witwatersrand</a> (Wits) in <a href="/wiki/Johannesburg" title="Johannesburg">Johannesburg</a>, <a href="/wiki/South_Africa" title="South Africa">South Africa</a>. He officially assumed the position of Vice-Chancellor on 1 June 2013 when the term of his predecessor <a href="/wiki/Loyiso_Nongxa" title="Loyiso Nongxa">Loyiso Nongxa</a> ended. He is also a former deputy vice chancellor of the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Johannesburg" title="University of Johannesburg">University of Johannesburg</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-CenterForCivilSociety_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-CenterForCivilSociety-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-SchoolOfDevelopment_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-SchoolOfDevelopment-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-ChristianScienceMonitor20071116_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-ChristianScienceMonitor20071116-4"><span>[</span>4<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
